	<div class="clearfix lead1">
		<h2 class="type-display1 loud float-left lead">Buttons</h2>
		<div class="float-right">
			<p>
				Reference: <a href="https://www.google.com/design/spec/components/buttons.html">Material Design: Buttons</a>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row lead2">
		<div class="col3">
			<p>
				Use the <code>.button</code> class to style a button, input, link, or div as a button.
			</p>
			<p>
				There is also the <code>.loud</code> class to indicate importance, and the <code>.attn</code>
				class to grab the users attention. (The attn class should be limited to one per visual screen.)
			</p>
			<p>
				Use a <code>&lt;span></code> inside a <code>&lt;button></code> element to keep Internet Explorer
				from shifting the text when pressing the button. Note: this cannot be avoided for input type buttons
				and does not occur on link buttons.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col3-2">
			<div class="outline">
				<input type="button" value="button" class="button"/>
				<button class="button loud"><span>button</span></button>
				<a href="#" class="button attn">button</a>
			</div>
			<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;input type="button" value="button" class="button"/>
&lt;button class="button loud">&lt;span>button&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a href="#" class="button attn">button&lt;/a>	
</pre>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<h3 class="type-subhead2 lead">Flat buttons</h3>
	<div class="row lead1">
		<div class="col3">
			<p>
				Add a <code>.flat</code> class name for buttons already on a raised content area or an area.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col3-2">
			<div class="outline">
				<input type="button" class="button flat" value="button" />
				<button class="button flat loud"><span>button</span></button>
				<a href="#" class="button flat attn">button</a>
			</div>
			<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;input type="button" class="button flat" value="button" />
&lt;button class="button flat loud">&lt;span>button&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a href="#" class="button flat attn">button&lt;/a>	
</pre>
		</div>
	</div>
	

	<h3 class="type-subhead2 lead">Disabled Buttons</h3>
	<div class="row lead1">
		<div class="col3">
			<p>
				All buttons will style accordingly when adding the <code>[disabled]</code> attribute.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col3-2">
				<div class="outline">
					<input type="button" value="button" disabled class="button" />
					<button class="button loud" disabled><span>button</span></button>
					<a class="button attn" disabled>button</a>
					<input type="button" class="button flat" value="button" disabled />
					<button class="button flat loud" disabled><span>button</span></button>
					<a class="button flat attn" disabled>button</a>
				</div>
				<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;input type="button" value="button" disabled class="button" />
&lt;button class="button loud" disabled>&lt;span>button&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a class="button attn" disabled>button&lt;/a>
&lt;input type="button" class="button flat" value="button" disabled />
&lt;button class="button flat loud" disabled>&lt;span>button&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a class="button flat attn" disabled>button&lt;/a>
</pre>
		</div>
	</div>
		
	

	
	

	
	
	
