	<h1 class="type-display1 loud lead">Icon buttons</h1>
	<section class="lead">
		<div class="row lead1">
			<div class="col3">
				<p>
					To make an icon a button, add the <code>[role=button]</code> attribute,
					add a <code>[tabindex=0]</code> attribute for focus, and the <code>.iconbutton</code>
					class name.
				</p>
				<p>
					Buttons support the <code>.quiet</code>, <code>.loud</code>, <code>.attn</code>,
					and <code>.disabled</code> modifiers.
				</p>
				<p>
					If using more than one icon button consider putting them in a toolbar.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col3-2">
					<div class="outline">
						<i class="iconbutton icon-menu" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-plus" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-cogs" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-menu quiet" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-plus quiet" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-cogs quiet" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-menu loud" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-plus loud" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-cogs loud" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-menu attn" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-plus attn" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-cogs attn" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-menu disabled" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-plus disabled" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
						<i class="iconbutton icon-cogs disabled" role="button" tabindex="0"></i>
					</div>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;i class="iconbutton icon-menu" role="button" tabindex="0">&lt;/i>
</pre>
			</div>
		</div>

